"#\n"
"# .xsession/.xinitrc\n"
"#\n"
"# choose a window manager\n"
"#\n"
"\n"
"defaultwm=kde\n"
"#set the window manager to $1 if it was supplied\n"
"windowmgr=${1:-$defaultwm}\n"
"\n"
"#start the respective window managers\n"
"case ${windowmgr} in\n"
"  kde|kwm|kdestart)\n"
"\tWINDOWMANAGER=startkde\n"
"\t;;\n"
"  fvwm|fvwm2)\n"
"\tWINDOWMANAGER=fvwm2\n"
"\t;;\n"
"\n"
"  fvwm95)\n"
"\tWINDOWMANAGER=fvwm95\n"
"\t;;\n"
"\n"
"  *)    WINDOWMANAGER=windowmgr   # default for unknown wm's\n"
"\n"
"esac\n"
"\n"
"#\n"
"# load resources\n"
"#\n"
"\n"
"if [ -f /usr/X11R6/lib/X11/Xmodmap ]; then\n"
"    xmodmap /usr/X11R6/lib/X11/Xmodmap\n"
"fi\n"
"\n"
"if [ -f ~/.Xmodmap ]; then\n"
"    xmodmap ~/.Xmodmap\n"
"fi\n"
"\n"
"if [ -f ~/.Xdefaults ]; then\n"
"    xrdb -merge ~/.Xdefaults\n"
"fi\n"
"\n"
"if [ -f ~/.Xresources ]; then\n"
"    xrdb -merge ~/.Xresources\n"
"fi\n"
"# \n"
"# finally start the window manager\n"
"#\n"
"exec $WINDOWMANAGER"

#: index.docbook:744
msgid "Building and Installing kdm"
msgstr "Compilation et installation de &kdm;"

#: index.docbook:746
msgid ""
"&kdm; is part of the KDE project. The various component parts of the KDE "
"project are broken into sections, called packages. &kdm; is part of the "
"package called kdebase. You can get KDE source code from various Linux and "
"BSD distribution CDs, or by download from <ulink "
"url=\"http://www.kde.org\">www.kde.org</ulink> or its mirrors. If you have "
"an out-of-date source code tree, you can use one of the KDE cvsup servers to "
"bring it up-to-date whilst using minimal network bandwidth."
msgstr ""
"&kdm; fait partie du projet &kde;. Les différents éléments composant le "
"projet &kde; sont scindés en sections appelées paquetages. Vous trouverez "
"&kdm; dans le paquetage nommé <quote>kdebase</quote>. Les codes sources de "
"&kde; sont disponibles sur certaines distributions Linux/BSD ou au "
"téléchargement, sur <ulink url=\"http://www.kde.org\">www.kde.org</ulink> "
"(ou un miroir). Si vous êtes en possession de code source provenant d'une "
"<quote>branche</quote> obsolète, il vous est possible d'utiliser les "
"serveurs cvsup de &kde; afin de les mettre à jour sans pour autant "
"monopoliser toute votre bande passante réseau."

#: index.docbook:755
msgid ""
"Before building kdebase, you must have built and installed (in this order) "
"version 2 of the qt library and the KDE packages kde-qt-addon, kdesupport "
"and kdelibs."
msgstr ""
"Avant de compiler kdebase, vous devrez avoir installé (dans l'ordre)&nbsp;: "
"la version 2 des bibliothèques QT, les paquetages &kde; "
"<quote>kde-qt-addon</quote>, kdesupport et enfin kdelibs."

#: index.docbook:759
msgid ""
"In order to build any of the above, you must already have the X Window "
"System installed, together with a C++ compiler and the GNU configuration "
"tools <application>configure</application>, "
"<application>automake</application> and <application>autoconf</application>."
msgstr ""
"Pour être en mesure de compiler tout ce qui vient d'être cité, votre "
"système devra être pourvu de X Window, d'un compilateur C++ et des outils "
"de configuration GNU <application>configure</application>, "
"<application>automake</application> et <application>autoconf</application>"

#: index.docbook:764
msgid ""
"If the last few paragraphs seemed like a foreign language, then either you "
"have strayed into an Inappropriate Area of this handbook, or you are about "
"to undergo a Great Learning Experience."
msgstr ""
"S'il vous apparaît que les derniers paragraphes sont écrits dans un "
"incompréhensible et mystérieux dialecte, c'est que&nbsp;: soit vous vous "
"êtes égaré dans une partie de ce manuel qui ne correspond pas à vos "
"attentes&nbsp;; soit vous êtes sur le point de partir dans une aventure "
"très enrichissante pour votre culture informatique."

#: index.docbook:768
msgid ""
"If you managed to satisfy all of the prerequisites, you are unlikely to have "
"any problems with building and installing kdebase. &kdm; is installed in "
"your \"<filename>$KDEDIR/bin</filename>\" directory."
msgstr ""
"Si vous avez respecté tous les pré-requis, la compilation et "
"l'installation de kdebase ne devrait poser aucun problème. &kdm; sera "
"installé dans votre répertoire "
"<quote><filename>$KDEDIR/bin</filename></quote>."

#: index.docbook:772
msgid ""
"<command>make <option>install</option></command> will overwrite your "
"previous <filename>kdmrc</filename>."
msgstr ""
"La commande <command>make <option>install</option></command> écrasera le "
"fichier <filename>kdmrc</filename> courant."

